GIT COMMANDS : 

How to check git version ==> git --version
How to initialize the git ==> git init --> Once initialized it will create .git directory.
They are three logical areas :

working-Area								Staging-Area				Local-Area
Created files in the code of the location ---> git add       ------> git commit -m "comment"



To add the files into the staging area ==> git add
To check status of git staging or not ==> git status
to add the source code files into the local area ==> git commit -m "comment" (-m means message)
[Oto stage and commit at a time ==> git commit -a -m "<message>"

For developing java projects source code developer will use IDE's :
Developer will use the IDE's ==> Popular IDE's Eclipse, Intellij,VSC,Atom
IDE's ==> Integrated Development Environments


How to configure the github user name and email
git config --global user.name "<user name>"
git config --global user.email "<user mail>"

how to check commit id's in the git ==> git log
How to check last 2 commit id's in the git ==> git log -2
To listout the user details in the git. ==> git config --global --list
How to check no.of users are modified particular file ==> git log <file name>

How to configure git hub repo into local repository.
Syntax : git remote add <alias name> <git hub repo url>
Ex : git remote add wm https://github.com/MSRSOFTWARE/wallmart.git

to check git remote repository url's ==> git remote -v


How to push the source code into git remote repository
git push <alias name> <branch name>
git push wm master
